type: dataset
title: MoonGen Setup Scripts for L2 Performance Testing
abstract: ' This experiment involved setting up two nodes (cesis and nida) with environment
  scripts and resetting them to a clean state using specified live images. The methodology
  included preparing the test environment by installing dependencies, cloning repositories,
  building software, configuring system parameters like hugetlbfs and disabling turbo
  boost for stable performance. Subsequently, network traffic was generated via MoonGen
  scripts, which captured timing metrics during L2 forwarding tests. Evaluation focused
  on measuring packet latency under varying rates and sizes while automatically recording
  energy consumption to assess efficiency.'
